    public class MsgPluralRemainderNode
extends AbstractSoyNode
implements SoyNode.MsgSubstUnitNode
    Node representing a 'remainder' section in a 'plural' block.

    Important: Do not use outside of Soy code (treat as superpackage-private).

        public String getBaseVarName()
        Description copied from interface: SoyNode.MsgSubstUnitNode
        Returns the base var name for this substitution unit. (For a placeholder, this is the base placeholder name.)

        Note: This isn't quite correct semantically. It's conceivable that a new type of substitution unit in the future could have multiple vars. But until that happens, this simpler model is sufficient.
